entry.title: The Advanced Television Services Regulations 1996
entry.summary: These Regulations implement the provisions of Directive 95/47/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council on the use of standards for the transmission of television signals (O.J. No. L281, 23.11.95, p. 51; “the Directive”), with the exception of Article 1, and Article 2 to the extent that it affects broadcasters other than the British Broadcasting Corporation (“the BBC”). The very general obligations under Article 1 are implemented by, and in the exercise of the powers conferred by, the Broadcasting Act 1996 (c. 55), and the requirements of Article 2 in relation to those other broadcasters are implemented by section 142 of that Act.

entry.title: The European Communities (Iron and Steel Employees Re-adaptation Benefits Scheme) (No. 2) (Amendment) Regulations 1996
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the existing powers of the Secretary of State under the Scheme established by the European Communities (Iron and Steel Employees Re-adaptation Benefits Scheme) (No. 2) Regulations 1988 (“the 1988 Regulations”), as continued in force by the European Communities (Iron and Steel Employees Re-adaptation Benefits Scheme) (No. 2) (Scheme Termination) Regulations 1994, by establishing a Supplemental Scheme to replace weekly payments under the 1988 Regulations by a lump sum payment to steel employees who are made redundant on or after 1 April 1996. The alternative pension option for redundant employees who are men aged 55 and over and women aged 50 and over in regulation 6 of the 1988 Regulations is retained.

entry.title: The Arbitration Act 1996 (Commencement No.1) Order 1996
entry.summary: With one exception, this Order brings into force the provisions of the Arbitration Act 1996. Those provisions necessary to enable the substantive provisions to be brought into force are commenced immediately. The substantive provisions come into force on 31st January 1997. Commencement is subject to transitional provisions designed to ensure continuity of legal proceedings and to preserve the current law on what are known as “honourable engagement” clauses in relation to existing agreements.
